reviews.review_text: I camped out  in a  winabago for 3 nites in the  Univ. of penn  parking lot..the  place  itself  had crappy acoustics..but  the  spectrum  was occupied.My  aud is  a  nuemann U-86 w/ 30 ft. seperation FOB ..it was  also  the  first  time  the weekend gigs(that i  noticed) started  to  sell  out  severely ie:more i need  a  miracle people there

love this show The first set is extra strong...

one of my favorites from 84

check it out it sounds great.

Venue Interesting venue with strange acoustics. I recall all three shows being very average...
There was lots of room to dance in the back on each side inside the auditorium though.

Skip it. First let me say I'm not a big fan of Brent Mydland. His DX7 seems to be set on the 'glockenspiel' for the majority of show, and his tinkling style of playing is particularly distracting.

The audio is the tinny 'stadium' quality in contrast to the warm sound of many earlier shows. There are probably great shows into the 80's but this isn't one of them.

Also, where is Phil in the mix? His bass is totally absent! A show without good Phil is not a good show.

Free one My girlfriend and I tried like hell to get tickets for the show and on our way back to the car we looked so dejected the security guard let walk through down the side of the building to get back to the parking lot. We spotted an open door and walked in the show. We only missed the first two songs. The show was average but it gets and extra star for the good karma.

? the show is decent, not horrible and not spectacular

dude, get a life man, the grateful dead gave us several years or their free soundboards, and while it sucks theyre gone, its their decision.

the dead are all about having a great time and enjoying the music, so stop being such a buzzkill protesting their shows because you cant get free music...other wise i expect to see you at basically every single concert of every single band in the world who doesnt give out free soundboards anymore.

Listen to the difference between this crappy AUD recording, and the sweet SBD recording....  ok i get it, bobby and the boys want to make some $$.

Jesus all this great freakin music and no one can touch it?  thats bullsh*t.
Thanks for posting Nice upgrade to my old cassette from 1984!  Thanks.

I just don't get it..... ....The pissing and moaning about the boards. The Dead are the ONLY band of significance to allow there audience to download their boards for YEARS. 

Yet, the band is not touring and the cash flow has stopped and now they have another cash flow to sustain lives. 

You can STILL listen to the BOARDS for free- unlike most other bands. Ok, so it is not the pristine quality you like on your 10K stereo system. 

Jeez, those that piss and moan about boards are the reason that .....well....never mind. I have my own glass house. 

Truth be told, I LOVE listening to the bad imperfections of the audience quality tapes. For those that want the sound board, you are the ones that pick out the imperfect notes and poor singing and what not. After 250 shows under my belt, I will beg of you to just go find another band that is even willing to let you listen for free. 

Peace and One Love
Strong Effort This is a good solid show--5 days after my first show (Hampton 4/14)--with many Dead classics on offer.  Birdsong, China>Rider, Estimated, and Wharf Rat are particularly hot.
